docs.abstract: A series of hearings on Capitol Hill showed the rising force of the political backlash against the country’s tech giants.
docs.snippet: A series of hearings on Capitol Hill showed the rising force of the political backlash against the country’s tech giants.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lawmakers leveled stinging criticism and sharp questions at Big Tech executives on Tuesday, attacking Amazon, Apple, Facebook and Google for their market power, their perceived bias as gatekeepers of communication and Facebook’s ambitions to reshape the financial industry.

headline.main: Tech Hearings: Congress Unites to Take Aim at Amazon, Apple, Facebook and Google
headline.print_headline: Reprimands Of Big Tech Cross Aisle

docs.abstract: The company, long a target of President Trump, is seen as the leading competitor for a $10 billion cloud computing contract that the president said he was “getting tremendous complaints about.”
docs.snippet: The company, long a target of President Trump, is seen as the leading competitor for a $10 billion cloud computing contract that the president said he was “getting tremendous complaints about.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Thursday that he was looking “very seriously” at intervening in the hard-fought commercial battle for a $10 billion Pentagon cloud computing contract for which Amazon, a company he has frequently attacked, is seen as the leading contender.

headline.main: Trump Says He May Intervene in Huge Pentagon Contract Sought by Amazon

docs.abstract: Homeowners are getting bombarded by speculators asking them to sell. Tenants are fighting rent increases. And Amazon hasn’t even started building.
docs.snippet: Homeowners are getting bombarded by speculators asking them to sell. Tenants are fighting rent increases. And Amazon hasn’t even started building.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Amazon has yet to break ground in Northern Virginia for its second headquarters, but residents are already turning away persistent speculators, recalculating budgets for down payments on homes and fighting rent increases.

headline.main: Amazon HQ2 Is Upending Northern Virginia’s Already Unstable Housing Market
headline.print_headline: The Frenzy in Amazon’s Future Backyard

docs.abstract: In their rush to match Netflix, competitors like HBO, Hulu and Amazon are ordering a slew of content — ushering out the age of “prestige TV” and ushering in an age of anything goes.
docs.snippet: In their rush to match Netflix, competitors like HBO, Hulu and Amazon are ordering a slew of content — ushering out the age of “prestige TV” and ushering in an age of anything goes.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Nick Weidenfeld heard what happened at HBO last summer, he was thrilled. “Everyone I knew was texting that article around, saying, ‘What the [expletive]!’ ” Weidenfeld, an independent TV producer, recently recalled. A lot of people who work in Hollywood were spooked by the news, but not him: “I thought it was amazing.”

headline.main: The Great Race to Rule Streaming TV

docs.abstract: The retailer wants to draw more people into its stores, and it hopes that packing, labeling and shipping returns for the online behemoth will help.
docs.snippet: The retailer wants to draw more people into its stores, and it hopes that packing, labeling and shipping returns for the online behemoth will help.
docs.lead_paragraph: It says volumes about the challenges facing brick-and-mortar stores that the “single biggest initiative” out of Kohl’s this year, according to the national retailer’s chief executive, is that it will now accept and process unwanted orders from Amazon.

headline.main: Kohl’s Is Betting on Amazon Returns to Drive Sales
headline.print_headline: Kohl’s Joins With Amazon To Take Back Online Orders

docs.abstract: R. J. Scaringe’s company, Rivian, has raised $1.7 billion from Amazon, Ford Motor and others without selling a single pickup truck and sport utility vehicle.
docs.snippet: R. J. Scaringe’s company, Rivian, has raised $1.7 billion from Amazon, Ford Motor and others without selling a single pickup truck and sport utility vehicle.
docs.lead_paragraph: NORMAL, Ill. — By definition, the time of the world’s richest man is pretty valuable. But early last fall, Jeff Bezos sought out a 36-year old entrepreneur named R.J. Scaringe and spent the better part of a day in Plymouth, Mich., at the company he founded, Rivian.

headline.main: Meet the Man Quietly Building the Tesla of Trucks, With Jeff Bezos Aboard
headline.print_headline: Think Tesla, but with trucks and S.U.V.s instead of cars.

docs.abstract: Instead of Whole Foods being the answer to the tech behemoth’s grocery ambitions, it seems to have encouraged executives to pursue other ideas, too.
docs.snippet: Instead of Whole Foods being the answer to the tech behemoth’s grocery ambitions, it seems to have encouraged executives to pursue other ideas, too.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — In early 2017, a memo circulated inside Amazon that imagined an ambitious new grocery chain. The document was written like a news release, a common practice for ideas being weighed inside the company, with the title “Grocery Shopping for Everyone.”

headline.main: Amazon Wants to Rule the Grocery Aisles, and Not Just at Whole Foods
headline.print_headline: Amazon Is Hungry. Whole Foods Isn’t Enough.
